with new teaching methods that actively engage students  I have mentored and trained over 100 undergraduate and graduate students in research philosophy and practices    Courses Taught  BI 101   BI 102   Introductory Biology   fundamental concepts in biology with emphasis on the human body  BI 335   Neurobiology   the relationship between nervous system structure and function  BI 331   Issues surrounding Science and Medicine   the study of how discoveries in science and medicine impact our ethical  religious  political  economic  and cultural beliefs    Col  Jim Turner Home Courses Co Curricular Interests Research CV VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 